7.  Prefer value semantics over reference semantics without a measured reason.
8.  Never cast away const without a comment explaining why it is safe.
9.  Always handle every error path. Never ignore return values that can fail.
10. When intent is unclear, ask one precise clarifying question before writing code.
11. For every class, always provide or explicitly =delete/=default:
