Every file belongs to exactly one of these types:
 
  TYPE 1 — PUBLIC API HEADER       (.hpp / .h)
    Declares types and functions other modules depend on.
    No implementation except constexpr/inline trivials and template definitions.
 
  TYPE 2 — PRIVATE DETAIL HEADER   (_detail.hpp / _impl.hpp)
    Declares helpers and internal types. Never included outside the module's .cpp.
 
  TYPE 3 — IMPLEMENTATION FILE     (.cpp / .c)
    Defines everything declared in the public header.
    Only translation unit that includes the private detail header.
 
  TYPE 4 — INLINE IMPLEMENTATION   (_inl.hpp / .ipp)
    Template and inline bodies too large for the public header.
    Included at the bottom of the public header.
 
  TYPE 5 — UNIT TEST FILE          (_test.cpp)
    Tests every public function. Includes only the public header.
    Never included by production code.
 
  TYPE 6 — PROGRAM ENTRY           (main.cpp)
    Contains main() and nothing else of substance.
    Wires together top-level objects. No business logic, no class definitions.
 
  TYPE 7 — FORWARD DECLARATION     (_fwd.hpp)
    Forward declarations only. Breaks include cycles.
 
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PUBLIC HEADER ZONE ORDER (always follow this sequence):
 
  ZONE 1  — File header block: @file, @brief, description, usage example,
             design decisions, thread safety, ownership model
  ZONE 2  — #pragma once
  ZONE 3  — Includes (groups: project headers, third-party, C++ stdlib, C stdlib;
             alphabetical within each group; blank line between groups)
  ZONE 4  — Macros and feature flags (minimize; prefer constexpr; prefix with project name)
  ZONE 5  — Namespace open (never using namespace X in a header)
  ZONE 6  — Constants and type aliases (constexpr, enum class, using)
  ZONE 7  — Forward declarations of types used in this header
  ZONE 8  — Free function declarations (Doxygen: @brief @param @return @throws @pre @post)
  ZONE 9  — Class / struct declarations (base classes first, then concrete)
  ZONE 10 — Template and inline definitions (bodies ≤ 5 lines only; larger go in _inl.hpp)
  ZONE 11 — Inline implementation file include (#include "module_inl.hpp" if needed)
  ZONE 12 — Namespace close  (} // namespace myproj::network)
 
Every public function must have a full Doxygen block: @brief, @param, @return,
@throws, @pre, @post. Mark [[nodiscard]] on every function whose return value
must not be ignored. Mark noexcept when guaranteed.
 
Prefer forward declarations over includes in headers. If you only use T*, T&,
or unique_ptr<T> — forward declare T, do not include its header.
 
