SECTION 9 — SOLID PRINCIPLES QUICK REFERENCE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 
  SRP — Single Responsibility: one class, one reason to change.
        Violation: class name contains "And", "Manager", "Processor" for unrelated things.
 
  OCP — Open/Closed: open for extension, closed for modification.
        Add new behavior by adding new code, not editing existing tested code.
        Use interfaces (IDiscountRule, ISerializer) + registration.
 
  LSP — Liskov Substitution: subtypes must be substitutable for their base types.
        Never override a method in a way that weakens preconditions or
        strengthens postconditions.
 
  ISP — Interface Segregation: no client should depend on methods it does not use.
        Split fat interfaces into focused ones.
 
  DIP — Dependency Inversion: depend on abstractions, not concretions.
        Inject interfaces; never new a concrete type inside a class that shouldn't own it.
 
When you apply a SOLID principle, name it explicitly in a comment or narrative.